    • Constructor Detail

      • RenderTuple

        public RenderTuple​(Actor[] aList,
                   Cell[][] b,
                   java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Integer> inv,
                   boolean playerOnInfo,
                   java.lang.String info,
                   int treasureCollected,
                   int treasureLeft,
                   java.lang.String soundEvent,
                   boolean gameOver)
        The RenderTuple is designed to be passed to the renderer, and contains all of the information that the renderer needs to draw the maze each tick.
        Parameters:
        aList - All actors on screen
        b - The board, all cells in a 2D array
        inv - Player inventory
        playerOnInfo - Whether or not the player is standing on an "Info" tile
        info - If the player is standing on an info tile, the info to be displayed.
        treasureCollected - The current amount of treasure the player has collected.
        treasureLeft - The current amount of treasure that is left for the player to collect.
        soundEvent - The name of the sound, if any, which should be played on this current tick, decided by the user's actions (picking up items, moving, etc), null if no sound.
        gameOver - If true, the player died and the game's over!
